{"_id":"BE6BbizNfbKTzx9Z","name":"Sword Dancing","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Sword Dancing</p>\n<p>You take +1 to Defy Danger when duelling, dancing, or anything else relying on impeccable footwork or graceful bladework.</p>\n<p>You add the following option to Sword Magic:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Dance or dodge gracefully out of harm&rsquo;s way with perfect form.</li>\n</ul>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Spellblade","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"EEPilXsLoJ2oMXTf","name":"The Spellblade","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"class","data":{"name":"","description":"<h2>The Spellblade</h2>\n<p>Stop me if you&rsquo;ve heard this one before. A young hero, full of promise, wields the magical blade and slays the dragon. Sound familiar? What they don&rsquo;t tell you is how much work it is. Spare a thought for all these people who just don&rsquo;t get it. It&rsquo;s not that while they were all at the tavern you were studying the blade. It&rsquo;s not just that you wanted it more. It&rsquo;s that you stay awake at night, running over the forms in your head. It&rsquo;s that you learned how to summon forth magical power and then thought to yourself &ldquo;what if I did this with a sword, too&rdquo;.</p>\n<p>It&rsquo;s that when your arms were too sore from training, you took out some metamagical treatises and read as much as you could.</p>\n<p>So yeah, you could say you&rsquo;re a little driven. But that&rsquo;s the way it goes - the winners write the history books, and you&rsquo;ve always wanted to be an author. You&rsquo;ll make sure the rest of them get a footnote, at least.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Names</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Human: Aragon, Baelor, Musashi, Joan, Shae, Zyzax, Quemora, Athenae</li>\n<li>Construct: Copper, Argent, Bottle, Oak, Patience, Strength, Cherry, Anchor</li>\n<li>Elf: Denethor, Ithilien, Gisha, Ylyndar, Elryc, Arwen, Galadriel, Hrontir, Vanue</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Look</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>BODY: Lithe, Musclebound, Broken, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>EYES: Stormy, Steely, Haunted, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>HAIR: Styled, Wild, Bald, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>SWORD: Etched, Ornate, Battle-scarred, or _ ___________</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Bond</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>I could teach _____________ a thing or two about swordplay. Or spellcraft. Or both.</li>\n<li>______________ is a trusted companion - they deserve a place in the epics, with me.</li>\n<li>______________ and I are no strangers to mortal danger and great adventure. I want to work together to seek our fortune.</li>\n<li>I appreciate _____________&rsquo;s efforts, but we're clearly not cut from the same cloth. I can show them how it&rsquo;s done.</li>\n<li>If I&rsquo;m not careful, _____________ might turn out to be even more famous than me.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Gear</h2>\n<p>O muse, tell me - what did they carry with them?</p>\n<p>Your Sorcerous Blade ( close, 1 weight), describe it or don&rsquo;t: ____________________________________</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose your armor:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Leather Armor ( 1 armor, w orn, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Shield ( +1 armor, 1 weight)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose two:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>20 coins</li>\n<li>Dungeon Rations ( 5 uses, ration, 1 weight), Uses left: 5</li>\n<li>Adventuring Gear (5 uses, 1 weight), Uses left: 5</li>\n<li>Two Healing Potions (0 weight)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>About The Spellblade</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Sorcerous Blade\n<ul>\n<li>It doesn&rsquo;t have to be a sword. Swords hold a lot of symbolic weight, but it doesn&rsquo;t have to be a sword.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Sword Magic<br />\n<ul>\n<li>This move is intended to work both in a reactive capacity (e.g., when the GM describes what is happening, the Spellblade can say &ldquo;Aha! I spend one hold to do -&rdquo;) but it can also be used purely proactively (e.g. when this move triggers, the Spellblade uses their hold to immediately produce an effect). This move requires more narrative justification than Hack &amp; Slash however, and many things can cause the Spellblade to lose hold prematurely (including making any other move or perhaps the result of someone making a move against the Spellblade). In addition, the Spellblade explicitly can&rsquo;t choose two options at once - as soon as the Spellblade spends hold to make a choice, the spotlight shifts to someone else. This move is based heavily off of the move Neutralize from Fraser Simon&rsquo;s excellent game The Veil.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Make History\n<ul>\n<li>The Spellblade has final say about what kind of events this move will trigger for, but often the trigger requires other people (or events that other people are responsible for).</li>\n<li>For the first option, if any allies choose that they&rsquo;d like someone&rsquo;s attention, they can choose whose they&rsquo;d like, even if their choice is different than the Spellblade&rsquo;s.</li>\n<li>For the last option, the Spellblade declares the nature of the connection and who or what it&rsquo;s between, and the other players (including the GM) decide who would know more. Players are allowed to select their own character.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Stormbringer<br />\n<ul>\n<li>GM&rsquo;s discretion, but think of the Barbarian&rsquo;s move Smash! and how much freedom that gives the player.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The Hero Of This Story<br />\n<ul>\n<li>On a 7-9, &ldquo;held responsible&rdquo; doesn&rsquo;t mean that the Spellblade is believed to have perpetrated everything, but that they are personally accountable, through their action or inaction, for what is going on.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","races":{"0":{"label":"Good","description":"Give up personal wealth or power for the greater good."},"1":{"label":"Neutral","description":"Defeat a powerful personal foe."},"2":{"label":"Evil","description":"Choose glory, fame, or power over compassion."},"3":{"label":"???","description":""}},"alignments":{"0":{"label":"Human","description":"Tales of your legend are already beginning to spread. When you enter a new settlement, someone whoâ€™s heard of you has a job for you."},"1":{"label":"Construct","description":"You might now pursue your own goals, but you were made as a weapon of war. When you Spout Lore or Discern Realities about war or its history, take +1."},"2":{"label":"Elf","description":"Magic is as natural to you as breathing. When you focus with your sorcerous blade, it becomes attuned to magic, and will gravitate gently towards magic items."},"3":{"label":"???","description":""}},"equipment":{"0":{"label":"O muse, tell me - what did they carry with them?","mode":"radio","items":["PTXRDdM3Y5wKmRPD"]},"1":{"label":"Choose your armor:","mode":"checkbox","items":["oGiXIqNQbukIjf06","FkfxRU6NiOzEzkIy"]},"2":{"label":"Choose two:","mode":"checkbox","items":["6JcOoZ8CNqYxLgyQ","YwHV7WYzTPSAOorl","CMhNmAwhLVZk9lfq"]}},"hp":8,"load":9,"damage":"d10"},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"EP5Jyn4DkZqhsrti","name":"The Sword In The Stone","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>The Sword In The Stone</p>\n<p>Requires: Sword Ritual</p>\n<p>When you perform your Sword Ritual, you may tell the GM the enchantment you are attempting to bestow.</p>\n<p>Enchantments are always possible, but the GM will give you one to four of the following conditions</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It&rsquo;s going to take days/weeks/months</li>\n<li>First you must ___</li>\n<li>You&rsquo;ll need help from ___</li>\n<li>It will require a lot of money</li>\n<li>The best you can do is a lesser version, unreliable and l imited</li>\n<li>You and your allies will risk danger from ___</li>\n<li>You&rsquo;ll have to disenchant ___ to do it</li>\n</ul>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Spellblade","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"Sword Ritual","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"KAXEJZaKBvNsemOr","name":"Might And Magic","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Might And Magic</p>\n<p>Requires: Sword and Sworcery</p>\n<p>Take another move from the Fighter class list that isn&rsquo;t a multiclass move.</p>","choices":"","moveType":"advanced","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":""},"success":{"value":""}},"class":"The Spellblade","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"Sword and Sworcery","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"MvY2z8PMQS0bXley","name":"Make History","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Make History</p>\n<p>The first time each session (your call) when you make yourself a part of something bigger than you, a legendary story, powerful magic, history in the making, etc, roll.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, choose one.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, two.</p>\n<p>Whatever you choose, you become entangled, entwined, and implicated in whatever&rsquo;s happening.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You and any of your allies get the attention of whoever you&rsquo;d like.</li>\n<li>You make an opening, and your allies take +1 ongoing while acting on it.</li>\n<li>You learn a connection between what&rsquo;s going on and another faction or event - declare it, and the other players will declare who knows more.</li>\n</ul>","choices":"","moveType":"starting","rollFormula":"","moveResults":{"failure":{"value":""},"partial":{"value":"<p>On a 7-9, choose one.</p>\n<p>Whatever you choose, you become entangled, entwined, and implicated in whatever&rsquo;s happening.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You and any of your allies get the attention of whoever you&rsquo;d like.</li>\n<li>You make an opening, and your allies take +1 ongoing while acting on it.</li>\n<li>You learn a connection between what&rsquo;s going on and another faction or event - declare it, and the other players will declare who knows more.</li>\n</ul>"},"success":{"value":"<p>On a 10+, two.</p>\n<p>Whatever you choose, you become entangled, entwined, and implicated in whatever&rsquo;s happening.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You and any of your allies get the attention of whoever you&rsquo;d like.</li>\n<li>You make an opening, and your allies take +1 ongoing while acting on it.</li>\n<li>You learn a connection between what&rsquo;s going on and another faction or event - declare it, and the other players will declare who knows more.</li>\n</ul>"}},"class":"The Spellblade","rollType":"BOND","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
